#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:123
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "About the FreeBSD Project"
msgstr ""
"关于FreeBSD项目\n"
"\n"
"=== Introduction\n"
"\n"
"The FreeBSD Project是一个自由的、以社区为驱动的操作系统项目，旨在为用户提供一个高度稳定、可靠和高性能的UNIX-like操作系统。它是一个开源项目，拥有庞大的开发者社区和众多贡献者。\n"
"\n"
"=== History\n"
"\n"
"FreeBSD项目源自于伯克利软件分发版的延续，最初由伯克利大学在1993年发布。自那时以来，项目一直在不断发展和改进，并且成为了一个功能强大且受欢迎的操作系统。\n"
"\n"
"=== Features\n"
"\n"
"FreeBSD项目的特点包括：\n"
"* 可移植性：FreeBSD可以运行在各种硬件平台上，包括x86、ARM、PowerPC等。\n"
"* 稳定性：它被广泛用于关键任务和大规模系统，以其卓越的稳定性和可靠性著称。\n"
"* 性能：FreeBSD优化了系统内核和网络栈，以提供卓越的性能。\n"
"* 安全性：它具有强大的安全特性，包括安全沙箱、强化的权限控制等，以保护系统免受恶意攻击。\n"
"* 弹性：FreeBSD采用模块化设计，使用户能够根据自己的需求进行定制和扩展。\n"
"\n"
"=== Documentation\n"
"\n"
"FreeBSD项目提供了详细且高质量的文档，包括手册、FAQ和帮助指南，以帮助用户了解和使用系统。\n"
"\n"
"=== Community\n"
"\n"
"FreeBSD社区拥有活跃的讨论邮件列表、IRC频道和在线论坛，用户可以在这里寻求帮助、分享经验和参与开发。\n"
"\n"
"=== Conclusion\n"
"\n"
"由于其出色的稳定性、可靠性和性能，FreeBSD是一款被广泛使用和推崇的操作系统，适用于各种应用场景。无论是个人使用还是企业级部署，FreeBSD都是一个优秀的选择。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:126
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The following section provides some background information on the project, "
"including a brief history, project goals, and the extref:{dev-"
"model}[development model] of the project."
msgstr "下面的部分提供了项目的一些背景信息，包括简要历史、项目目标以及项目的开发模式（extref:{dev-model}[开发模式]）。"

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:128
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "A Brief History of FreeBSD"
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 是一种类 UNIX 操作系统，具有稳定性、强大性能和高度可靠性的特点。它的历史可以追溯到 1970 年代早期的 UNIX 系统。\n"
"在 1993 年，一群来自加州大学伯克利分校的计算机科学家，基于 386BSD 操作系统创建了 FreeBSD。386BSD 是由 William Jolitz 和 Lynne Jolitz 开发的一种BSD 分支系统，旨在将 UNIX 功能带给个人电脑用户。\n"
"大约在 1994 年，FreeBSD 发布了第一个稳定版本，并且从那时起继续迅速发展和成熟。FreeBSD 团队致力于提供一个开放、自由的操作系统，为用户和开发人员提供强大的工具和环境。\n"
"随着时间的推移，FreeBSD 获得了广泛的认可，并发展成为一个强大而灵活的操作系统，用于各种用途，包括服务器、工作站和嵌入式系统。它在网络性能、安全性和稳定性方面取得了显著的突破，并被广泛应用于计算机科学、互联网、科研和商业领域。\n"
"今天，FreeBSD 仍然是一个活跃的开源项目，由全球的开发人员社区支持和维护。它继续不断改进和更新，以适应不断变化的计算机技术和需求。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:131
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD Project had its genesis in the early part of 1993, partially as "
"the brainchild of the Unofficial 386BSDPatchkit's last 3 coordinators: Nate "
"Williams, Rod Grimes and Jordan Hubbard."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD项目诞生于1993年初，部分地是由非官方的386BSDPatchkit的最后三位协调员Nate Williams、Rod "
"Grimes和Jordan Hubbard提出的构想。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:134
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The original goal was to produce an intermediate snapshot of 386BSD in order"
" to fix a number of problems that the patchkit mechanism was just not "
"capable of solving.  The early working title for the project was 386BSD 0.5 "
"or 386BSD Interim in reference to that fact."
msgstr ""
"最初的目标是创建386BSD的一个中间快照，以解决一些无法通过补丁机制解决的问题。该项目的早期工作标题是386BSD 0.5或386BSD "
"Interim，以此为参考。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:138
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"386BSD was Bill Jolitz's operating system, which had been up to that point "
"suffering rather severely from almost a year's worth of neglect.  As the "
"patchkit swelled ever more uncomfortably with each passing day, they decided"
" to assist Bill by providing this interim \"cleanup\" snapshot.  Those plans"
" came to a rude halt when Bill Jolitz suddenly decided to withdraw his "
"sanction from the project without any clear indication of what would be done"
" instead."
msgstr ""
"386BSD是Bill "
"Jolitz开发的操作系统，但此时由于几乎一年的疏忽而遭受了严重的问题。随着每一天过去，补丁包变得越来越庞大，他们决定通过提供这个临时的“清理”快照来帮助Bill。然而，当Bill"
" Jolitz突然决定撤销对该项目的支持，并没有明确表示将采取何种措施时，这些计划被迫中止。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:143
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The trio thought that the goal remained worthwhile, even without Bill's "
"support, and so they adopted the name \"FreeBSD\" coined by David Greenman."
"  The initial objectives were set after consulting with the system's current"
" users and, once it became clear that the project was on the road to perhaps"
" even becoming a reality, Jordan contacted Walnut Creek CDROM with an eye "
"toward improving FreeBSD's distribution channels for those many unfortunates"
" without easy access to the Internet.  Walnut Creek CDROM not only supported"
" the idea of distributing FreeBSD on CD but also went so far as to provide "
"the project with a machine to work on and a fast Internet connection.  "
"Without Walnut Creek CDROM's almost unprecedented degree of faith in what "
"was, at the time, a completely unknown project, it is quite unlikely that "
"FreeBSD would have gotten as far, as fast, as it has today."
msgstr ""
"三人组认为即使没有Bill的支持，目标仍然是值得的，因此他们采用了由David "
"Greenman创造的名字\"FreeBSD\"。在与系统当前用户协商之后，确定了初始目标，一旦清楚项目可能成为现实，Jordan就联系了Walnut "
"Creek CDROM，以改善FreeBSD的分发渠道，使那些没有方便访问互联网的人也能使用。Walnut Creek "
"CDROM不仅支持在光盘上分发FreeBSD，还提供了一台机器和高速互联网连接供项目使用。如果没有Walnut Creek "
"CDROM对当时一个完全不知名的项目几乎无与伦比的信任，FreeBSD几乎不可能取得如今的这么大的进展。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:147
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The first CD-ROM (and general net-wide) distribution was FreeBSD 1.0, "
"released in December of 1993.  This was based on the 4.3BSD-Lite (\"Net/2\")"
" tape from U.C. Berkeley, with many components also provided by 386BSD and "
"the Free Software Foundation.  It was a fairly reasonable success for a "
"first offering, and they followed it with the highly successful FreeBSD 1.1 "
"release in May of 1994."
msgstr ""
"第一张 CD-ROM （以及整个网络范围的）分发版是 FreeBSD 1.0，于 1993 年 12 月发布。它基于加州大学伯克利分校的 4.3BSD-"
"Lite (\"Net/2\") 磁带，同时也借鉴了 386BSD 和自由软件基金会提供的许多组件。作为首次发布，这是一个相当成功的尝试，并在 1994"
" 年 5 月发布了备受成功的 FreeBSD 1.1 版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:153
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Around this time, some rather unexpected storm clouds formed on the horizon "
"as Novell and U.C. Berkeley settled their long-running lawsuit over the "
"legal status of the Berkeley Net/2 tape.  A condition of that settlement was"
" U.C. Berkeley's concession that three files of Net/2 were \"encumbered\" "
"code and had to be removed as they were the property of Novell, who had in "
"turn acquired it from AT&T some time previously.  What Berkeley got in "
"return was Novell's \"blessing\" that the 4.4BSD-Lite release, when it was "
"finally released, would be declared unencumbered and all existing Net/2 "
"users would be strongly encouraged to switch.  This included FreeBSD, and "
"the project was given until the end of July 1994 to stop shipping its own "
"Net/2 based product.  Under the terms of that agreement, the project was "
"allowed one last release before the deadline, that release being FreeBSD "
"1.1.5.1."
msgstr ""
"在这个时候，诺维尔（Novell）和加州大学伯克利分校（U.C. "
"Berkeley）就有关伯克利Net/2软件的法律地位的长期纠纷达成了和解。和解协议的一个条件是，加州大学伯克利分校承认Net/2的三个文件属于\"有限制\"代码，必须移除，因为这些文件是诺维尔的财产，而诺维尔之前从AT&T那里收购了这些文件。作为交换，伯克利分校获得了诺维尔的\"祝福\"，即4.4BSD-"
"Lite的最终发布会被宣布为无限制的，并且强烈鼓励所有现有的Net/2用户切换到该版本。其中包括FreeBSD，该项目被给予截止日期为1994年7月底之前停止发行基于Net/2的产品。根据协议的条款，该项目被允许在截止日期前发布一次最后的版本，即FreeBSD"
" 1.1.5.1。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:158
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"FreeBSD then set about the arduous task of literally re-inventing itself "
"from a completely new and rather incomplete set of 4.4BSD-Lite bits.  "
"Although only three files having to do with System V shared memory and "
"semaphores were removed, many other changes and bug fixes had been made to "
"the BSD distribution, so it was a huge task to merge all the FreeBSD "
"developments into 4.4BSD-Lite.  It took the project until November of 1994 "
"to make this transition, and in December it released FreeBSD 2.0 to the "
"world.  Despite being still more than a little rough around the edges, the "
"release was a significant success and was followed by the more robust and "
"easier to install FreeBSD 2.0.5 release in June of 1995."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD开始了一项艰巨的任务，从一个全新且相对不完整的4.4BSD-Lite代码库中重新发展自己。尽管只有涉及System "
"V共享内存和信号量的三个文件被移除，BSD发行版已经进行了许多其他更改和错误修复，因此将所有FreeBSD的开发成果合并到4.4BSD-"
"Lite中是一项巨大的任务。项目直到1994年11月才完成了这个过渡，并于12月发布了FreeBSD "
"2.0。尽管该版本还有一些不完善之处，但发布取得了重大成功，并在1995年6月发布了更加稳定和易于安装的FreeBSD 2.0.5版本。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:160
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Since that time, FreeBSD has made a series of releases each time improving "
"the stability, speed, and feature set of the previous version."
msgstr "自那时以来，FreeBSD每次发布都会改进以前版本的稳定性、速度和功能集。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:162
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For now, long-term development projects continue to take place in the {rel-"
"head}-CURRENT (main) branch, and snapshot releases of {rel-head} are "
"continually made available from "
"link:https://download.freebsd.org/snapshots/[the snapshot server] as work "
"progresses."
msgstr ""
"目前，长期开发项目仍在{rel-head}-CURRENT（主要）分支上进行，并且在工作进展的同时，不断发布{rel-"
"head}的快照版本，可以从link:https://download.freebsd.org/snapshots/[快照服务器]获取。"

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:164
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Project Goals"
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 项目目标\n"
"\n"
"**摘要**\n"
"该文档描述了 FreeBSD 项目的目标和愿景。\n"
"\n"
"== 项目目标 ==\n"
"FreeBSD 项目的主要目标是开发一个稳定、可靠、高性能和高度可扩展的操作系统。\n"
"\n"
"以下是 FreeBSD 项目的具体目标：\n"
"\n"
"* **优秀的性能**：FreeBSD 致力于提供卓越的性能，以满足各种计算机应用的需求。\n"
"\n"
"* **可靠性和稳定性**：FreeBSD 的核心原则之一是提供可靠的操作系统，确保数据的安全性和系统的稳定性。\n"
"\n"
"* **可移植性**：FreeBSD 旨在保持跨不同硬件平台的可移植性，以便在不同的环境中广泛使用。\n"
"\n"
"* **安全性**：作为一个开放源代码项目，FreeBSD 致力于提供一个安全的操作系统，并及时响应安全漏洞和威胁。\n"
"\n"
"* **兼容性**：FreeBSD 的目标是保持与其他 UNIX-like 操作系统的兼容性，以简化软件移植和交互操作。\n"
"\n"
"* **社区合作**：FreeBSD 的发展一直依赖于一个开放、活跃和合作的社区，以持续改进和推动项目的发展。\n"
"\n"
"上述目标指导着 FreeBSD 项目的发展和决策，确保操作系统在未来能够继续为用户提供高品质的体验。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:170
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The goals of the FreeBSD Project are to provide software that may be used "
"for any purpose and without strings attached.  Many of us have a significant"
" investment in the code (and project) and would certainly not mind a little "
"financial compensation now and then, but we are definitely not prepared to "
"insist on it.  We believe that our first and foremost \"mission\" is to "
"provide code to any and all comers, and for whatever purpose, so that the "
"code gets the widest possible use and provides the widest possible benefit."
"  This is, we believe, one of the most fundamental goals of Free Software "
"and one that we enthusiastically support."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD项目的目标是提供可用于任何目的且无附加条件的软件。我们中的许多人在这个代码（和项目）上投入了相当多的精力，偶尔获得一些经济补偿并不介意，但我们绝对不会坚持要求。我们相信我们最重要的“使命”是向所有人提供代码，无论目的为何，以便代码得到最广泛的使用并提供最广泛的效益。我们认为这是自由软件最基本的目标之一，我们全力支持。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:173
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That code in our source tree which falls under the GNU General Public "
"License (GPL) or Library General Public License (LGPL) comes with slightly "
"more strings attached, though at least on the side of enforced access rather"
" than the usual opposite.  Due to the additional complexities that can "
"evolve in the commercial use of GPL software we do, however, prefer software"
" submitted under the more relaxed BSD license when it is a reasonable option"
" to do so."
msgstr ""
"在我们的源代码树中，根据 GNU General Public License（GPL）或 Library General Public "
"License（LGPL）的许可证的代码会附带更多限制条件，尽管至少强制访问是额外限制的一种，而不是通常的另一种限制。然而，由于商业使用GPL软件可能出现的额外复杂性，我们更倾向于在合理的情况下选择使用更宽松的BSD许可证提交软件。"

#. type: Title ===
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:175
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "The FreeBSD Development Model"
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 开发模型\n"
"\n"
"=== Introduction\n"
"\n"
"The FreeBSD operating system follows a unique, community-driven development model that promotes collaboration and open source principles. This model allows developers from around the world to contribute to the project and actively participate in its evolution.\n"
"\n"
"=== Core Team\n"
"\n"
"At the core of the FreeBSD development model is the Core Team, responsible for overseeing and coordinating the overall direction of the project. The Core Team consists of highly skilled individuals who are chosen based on their technical expertise and their commitment to the FreeBSD community.\n"
"\n"
"=== Comitters\n"
"\n"
"Comitters are FreeBSD developers who have been granted write access to the project's source code repository. They have the authority to directly commit changes to the codebase after rigorous peer review and approval from the Core Team. Comitters are responsible for maintaining the quality and stability of the FreeBSD system.\n"
"\n"
"=== Working Groups\n"
"\n"
"Working Groups are smaller teams of developers focused on specific aspects of FreeBSD development. These groups are formed to tackle specific challenges, introduce new features, or improve existing components of the operating system. Working groups promote collaboration and ensure that progress is made towards common goals.\n"
"\n"
"=== Release Engineering\n"
"\n"
"The release engineering team is responsible for managing the release process of FreeBSD. They coordinate the integration of new features, bug fixes, and security patches into each release. This team follows a strict schedule to ensure that stable and reliable versions of FreeBSD are made available to users.\n"
"\n"
"=== Communications and Decision Making\n"
"\n"
"The FreeBSD community relies heavily on mailing lists and online forums for communication and decision making. Discussions take place openly and transparently, and decisions are often made through a consensus of the community. This inclusive approach ensures that the voices of all contributors are heard and respected.\n"
"\n"
"=== Conclusion\n"
"\n"
"The FreeBSD development model has been instrumental in the success and longevity of the project. It fosters a collaborative and inclusive environment, allowing FreeBSD to continually evolve and improve as an open source operating system."

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:180
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The development of FreeBSD is a extref:{dev-model}[very open and flexible "
"process], being literally built from the contributions of thousands of "
"people around the world, as can be seen from our extref:{contributors}[list "
"of contributors].  FreeBSD's development infrastructure allows these "
"thousands of contributors to collaborate over the Internet.  We are "
"constantly on the lookout for new volunteers, and those interested in "
"becoming more closely involved should consult the article on "
"extref:{contributing}[Contributing to FreeBSD]."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD的开发是一个非常开放和灵活的过程，字面上是由全世界数以千计的人的贡献所建立的，可以从我们的[贡献者列表](contributors)中看出。FreeBSD的开发基础设施允许这些数以千计的贡献者通过互联网进行合作。我们始终在寻找新的志愿者，对于那些有兴趣更深入参与的人应该参考[关于贡献](contributing)的文章。"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/introduction/_index.adoc:182
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Useful things to know about the FreeBSD Project and its development process,"
" whether working independently or in close cooperation:"
msgstr ""
"了解FreeBSD项目及其开发流程的一些有用信息，无论是独立工作还是密切合作的情况下：\n"
"\n"
"- The FreeBSD Project is an open-source operating system project that focuses on providing a stable, secure, and high-performance operating system for various platforms.\n"
"（FreeBSD项目是一个开源操作系统项目，专注于为各种平台提供稳定、安全和高性能的操作系统。）\n"
"\n"
"- The project is governed by a core team that makes important decisions and ensures the overall development process is coherent and well-managed.\n"
"（该项目由核心团队管理，他们做出重要决策，并确保整个开发过程有条不紊、管理良好。）\n"
"\n"
"- The development process follows a hierarchical structure, with a primary focus on the 'head' branch, which contains the latest development work.\n"
"（开发流程遵循一种分层结构，主要关注“head”分支，其中包含最新的开发工作。）\n"
"\n"
"- Regular 'snapshot' releases are made available to users, providing them with stable and tested versions of the operating system.\n"
"（定期发布“快照”版本供用户使用，为他们提供稳定且经过测试的操作系统版本。）\n"
"\n"
"- Developers are encouraged to contribute to the project by submitting bug reports, fixing issues, and submitting new features.\n"
"（鼓励开发人员通过提交错误报告、修复问题和提供新功能来为项目做出贡献。）\n"
"\n"
"- The project uses various development tools, including version control systems like Git and Subversion, as well as a bug tracking system called GNATS.\n"
"（该项目使用各种开发工具，包括Git和Subversion等版本控制系统，以及一个名为GNATS的错误跟踪系统。）\n"
"\n"
"- The documentation for FreeBSD is comprehensive and is available in various formats, such as man pages, handbooks, and online resources.\n"
"（FreeBSD的文档全面，提供各种格式，如man页、手册和在线资源。）\n"
"\n"
"- The project has a strong focus on security, with regular security advisories and a security team dedicated to addressing vulnerabilities.\n"
"（该项目十分注重安全性，定期发布安全警报，并设有专门的安全团队解决漏洞。）\n"
"\n"
"- The FreeBSD community is active and supportive, providing forums, mailing lists, and conferences for users and developers to collaborate and share knowledge.\n"
"（FreeBSD社区活跃且支持性强，为用户和开发人员提供论坛、邮件列表和会议，以便进行合作和分享知识。）\n"
